---
import ToolLayout from '../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
const SITE = 'https://healthcalculation.com';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="Medical Disclaimer — HealthCalcs.com"
  description="Medical disclaimer for HealthCalcs.com. Our calculators provide estimates for informational purposes only and are not a substitute for professional medical advice."
  canonical={`${SITE}/disclaimer`}
>
  <div class="page-layout">
    <div class="main-col">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span>›</span><span>Medical Disclaimer</span>
      </nav>

      <h1>Medical Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="lead">Please read before using any calculator on this site.</p>

      <div class="card disc-card">
        <p class="disc-lead">
          ⚕️ <strong>The information on HealthCalcs.com is for general informational and
          educational purposes only.</strong> It is not intended as medical advice and does not
          replace the advice of a qualified healthcare professional.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2>Not a Substitute for Professional Advice</h2>
      <p>
        Always seek the advice of your physician, registered dietitian, or other qualified
        healthcare provider regarding any medical condition, dietary change, or fitness program.
        Never disregard professional medical advice or delay seeking it because of something you
        have read or calculated on this website.
      </p>

      <h2>Calculator Accuracy</h2>
      <p>
        Our calculators use clinically validated formulas (Mifflin-St Jeor, WHO BMI, AASM sleep
        guidelines). However, all results are <strong>population-level estimates</strong> and may
        not reflect your individual physiology. Factors such as genetics, medications, metabolic
        conditions, and hormonal status can cause significant variation.
      </p>
      <p>
        A ±10–15% variance from calculated values is normal. Use results as a starting point and
        adjust based on real-world feedback and professional guidance.
      </p>

      <h2>Calorie & Nutrition Information</h2>
      <p>
        Calorie targets presented are estimates derived from the Mifflin-St Jeor equation.
        Do not follow calorie targets that fall below 1,200 cal/day (women) or 1,500 cal/day
        (men) without direct supervision from a licensed healthcare provider.
      </p>

      <h2>BMI Limitations</h2>
      <p>
        BMI (Body Mass Index) is a screening tool only. It does not directly measure body fat
        and may misclassify muscular individuals. A BMI outside the "healthy" range is not a
        diagnosis. Consult your doctor for a comprehensive health evaluation.
      </p>

      <h2>Emergency Situations</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe you are experiencing a medical emergency, call 911 (US) or your local
        emergency services immediately. Do not use this website in place of emergency care.
      </p>

      <h2>Affiliate Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        Some pages contain links to third-party products or services. These are affiliate links —
        we may earn a commission if you purchase through them at no additional cost to you.
        Editorial content and calculator results are never influenced by affiliate relationships.
        We only recommend products we believe are genuinely helpful.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions or concerns? Email
        <a href="mailto:hello@healthcalculation.com">hello@healthcalculation.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="sidebar">
      <div class="card" style="font-size:13px;color:#374151">
        <p style="font-weight:700;margin-bottom:8px">⚕️ Key Points</p>
        <p>📋 Estimates, not diagnoses</p>
        <p>👨‍⚕️ Always consult a doctor</p>
        <p>📊 ±10–15% variance is normal</p>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0">🚨 Call 911 in emergencies</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<style>
  h1 { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  h2 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin: 24px 0 8px; }
  .disc-card { background: #fffbeb; border-color: #fde68a; }
  .disc-lead { font-size: 15px; color: #78350f; margin: 0; }
</style>
